Question: Why were you homeschooled ? Was there something wrong with your local school?
Answer:
No there was nothing wrong with the schools. However when michael our oldest brother and the oldest child of my siblings was young our mom, found an interview where a 14 year old girl  was talking about college and how she was just soaring and excelling. My mom was fascinated by her story,  but was a bit wary of the idea because homeschooling wasn't very common at the time in the early 90s. My mom however went to public schools and did not enjoy her experience at all. Due to bullying, and skipping grades she would sometimes be bored and waiting for the lecture to be over with. So she wanted us to advance at our own pace instead of being rushed or forced. And be able to skip grades if that was what was best for us. Her and dad decided to home school all of us from k-12 and developed their own curriculum which focused on Latin, greek, classic literature, catholic faith and critical thinking. Mom wanted us to have to learn to think for ourselves, to be curious and love learning, and to have strong moral compasses. she signed  us up for every activity possible in our  area- swim team, musical theatre, basketball, gymnastics, Boy Scouts and Girl Scouts, karate, and many more. We all grew up to be a loud, vibrant bunch. We were very well “socialized” and had a lot of friends. Most people didn’t guess we were homeschooled when they met us because of our social and people skills.
  

  To this day, we all count our homeschool experience as one of the greatest tools in our lives and careers. Because of homeschooling, we have had a lot of free time to learn instruments, practice singing and harmonizing, and write songs. Homeschooling gave us the space to be free to be ourselves. Being unique and independent was highly valued in the Cimorelli household; we were not told to “fit into the mold.” This ideal shaped our music and decisions for years to come

New video!!!
  

   https://youtu.be/k2YX49xa6Y8

This week with Lauren - 1/19
  
  I feel like I’m finally starting to level out a bit in life. I’ve been trying to achieve balance and peace for so long but I’ve consistently been anxious and overwhelmed and stressed pretty much all the time. Last week I talked about implementing new routines which I’ve been doing for about 3 weeks now and this week I feel like they’re actually working! I think I got the night routine down and my week structure down, but still working on a morning routine that works for me. The biggest thing I think that’s helping me is taking Monday and Wednesday night as self care nights. I don’t look at my phone, and I take the whole night from like 7:00 on to do whatever kind of relaxing/enjoyable things I wanna do. Not laying in my bed watching Netflix tho, stuff like doing a face mask, clean my room, taking a shower, dancing, songwriting, whatever it is just putting myself first in that time. Knowing that I have those nights coming up makes me more relaxed in general too cause if I’m feeling overwhelmed or stressed I’m like ok well I know on Monday and Wednesday I get to relax, so there’s a light at the end of this tunnel 🙏🏼 I’m also adopting a new mindset that’s like I can only do what I can do. I don’t need to do everything everyday. I identify what the most important things are to do for the week and then plan them in and if I don’t have time for them, I plan them into next week. I used to feel like the more I do, the more worth I have as a person, but that’s not true at all. At this point I would rather be relaxed and fulfilled, instead of doing as many things as I possibly can and then burning out all the time. Realizing too that when I’m relaxed and feel balanced, I do better work and I’m more creative so really it’s a win win. Also I released a music video yesterday for my song #BrownEyedBoys go check it out if you haven’t seen it! (Link in my bio) Thanks for coming to my ted talk 🙏🏼

Question: What were some of the turning points in your life? 🤔
Answer:
* 8 years old I started a career because my sister wanted to be in a band

  * few weeks later a manager from london wanted us to perform for her
  
  *she had us drive down to la to perform for her coworkers at island records
  
  * we got signed immediately and moved to malibu
  
  *while under this management label we have done many things and all such as working with songwriters and believe it not keshas mom
  
  *however in 2015, they tried to changed us into something we would never be and we felt drained and not wanting to do musoc anymore
  
  * we broke away from our label and went independent, moved to nashville
  
  *the older girls moved into their own apartment together while Dani and I lived in the family house
  
  *we later released our first album and many EPs later : up at night
  
  *did many tours over those years which included a European tour and south america tour
  
  * hit 5 million subscribers and still continue to impact people's life and spread our true meaning

Answer:
Dani has left the band to move on and pursue other dreams and journeys she has had for awhile. And its heartbreaking we know, but sisterhood comes first and we will always be sisters. This wasnt a rushed decision and nothing bad happened. She just wanted something different and we are glad she has been with us for the 10 years as she has done so much and impacted everyone in a positive way. No its not because of her husband this is something she has wanted for a long time. And we supoort her choice and will support her through it. However so much will change, and there will be a blank space and a missing puzzle piece. But Dani will still be involved with the cimfam, either randomly appearing in videos or supporting the new music, or cheering us on from the crowds. We didnt force her or kick her out of the band. And the door will always be open for her to come back if she wants. But the band is not leaving, we are going into 2020 as a five piece. Kinda like it was when we first started youtube then added our brother Michael in for a while then Dani joined in. ... So please no hate comments about any of this and understand that we are all hurting and upset because none of us wanted this and like dani says in before octobers gone, "maybe sometimes things just have to end".
  
  But she will still be active  on social media  and if you want to continue supporting us as a five piece thank you but you can also support Dani and follow her journey @ daniandemmyn on youtube

But some addressed their concerns in a way that was very harsh and made fun of the poster and the design claiming it was cheaply made, a waste of money etc. But little did they know the story behind it and just kept putting down the poster. Danielle cimorelli ( our youngest sister) who is only 19. Has became interested in graphic design lately and she's still learning how to do things involving that. We let her do the design of the poster and she thought it would be fun to create a poster out of it and expand her skills as well. Danielle has also done the header and designs for our youtube and our tour announcement, and even helped designed my orange merch as well as emmyns and max's. And I feel incredibly blessed that she has even offered to help with these things. As for a learner I think she does a great job, and her designs are really cute and matches with the aesthetic. However, I know have to deal with a very upset and hurt sister who just wanted to do something for thousands of people to enjoy and have fun creating it as well. ... This is why you must consider what you're about to post! Because we see a lot of those things even if you think we may not. And twitter has always been a toxic place for dani to be on that she stopped coming on completely and had to make a second account. Its sad that our fandom that is suppose to be a positive uplifting community has turned into something wrong don't even associate with. So I ask if you claim to be a fan of ours hut constantly say negative things about any of us, remove yourself from the fandom ... And don't associate with those trying to be positive as well in it.... Im just extremely disappointed and when it comes to.someone I care about like my sister. I feel I have to defend them. But please change your behavior and learn how to think about what you're saying before posting it and hurting someone...

Question: PAP 😉
Answer:
This week with Lauren - 12/7
  
  A couple days late, sorry lads lol tbh just been trying to catch my breath these last couple days!!!! Got home from the last stop of the Believe In You tour on Saturday night and let me tell you I have never slept more than I have in the last 2 days!!!!! This has been the most challenging and hectic month/2 months of maybe my entire life. It‘s like just when you think everything will calm down, there’s something else !!! Did not foresee all of this. Been working with my therapist a lot on using healthy coping strategies to deal with stress and big emotions. Definitely don’t always employ these strategies, but things like being honest with myself, taking time to process my thoughts and feelings (and allowing myself to feel those feelings and have those thoughts), and setting boundaries that I need to keep myself healthy (mentally and physically) even though it might inconvenience other people have been coming in clutch. I think the holidays/the end of the year is pretty hard for a lot of people. A lot of you guys have your finals for school right now, being around family can be really stressful, or trying to celebrate when you’ve lost a loved one or come from a broken home, or even just having your own personal struggles and not being able to enjoy what’s supposed to be the happiest time of year can be really hard. You’re not alone guys. And you don’t have to pretend like everything’s fine when it’s not. It’s okay to feel exactly however it is that you feel and there’s nothing wrong with you for feeling that way ❤️ p.s. the last video is from something really special we filmed ;)

Question: Give me some coins :(
Answer: I started releasing my solo music the beginning of this year (well, December 28th, 2018) and I had no idea what to expect from you guys. You guys are so supportive of our Cimorelli music, but I wasn’t sure what the reaction would be to my music. I was so scared of putting myself out there. Especially with my song “Running”. That was the first song I released. Not sure why I decided to start with the most vulnerable one 🙃 I remember when I announced it was coming out I was soooo nervous and for that whole week before it came out I could barely eat. Not only was it terrifying anticipating what people’s reactions might be, but at this point in my life I was a very private person. I didn’t like sharing struggles, or vulnerabilities with people. Especially not to strangers on the internet. I wrote this song when I was 17 with the sole intention of expressing my feelings about the situation I was in. I had no idea how to produce a song and not much of an idea how to write a song. My thought when I finished it was “There is no way I am ever realizing this. This is waaayy too personal.” 3 years later, my baby was about to come into the world. Every song on my EP #Orange came about the same way. The only thought I had while writing these was this: What is the most accurate way I can communicate the way that I am feeling right now? The response I got to all of these songs was OVERWHELMING. Especially to Running. It’s so humbling to see the support you guys have shown 😭 beyond grateful for you all and I’m SO excited to see what this next year brings 💜 also shoutout to Mexico 😘

This week with Lauren - 11/23
  
  Wow I’m actually posting 2 weeks in a row ! Who would’ve thot ! lol almost every pic in this is from last weekend bc this week was really hard!!! So much has been piling up on me and I wasn’t prepared for it. Didn’t have the routines / systems / schedules in place to be able to deal with so much. I pretty much just withdrew into myself and tried to make the world go away. Didn’t work that well bc the world still exists 🙃 still working through this slump tbh but I felt a lot better today after spending some time honestly connecting with some people yesterday and talking about what was going on and also being real with myself and talking to myself about what was going on lol seems like a no-brainer, but I do have a tendency to not check in with myself and see what’s going on, especially when I’m not feeling good. If you’re going through a hard time right now, which I know a lot of you are, just know I’m right there with you and we’ll get through it. ❤️ I wanna say thanks to everyone who supported our new merch launch / golden ticket week! I put my heart and soul into all of it and it’s been our most successful drop to date and that is really encouraging to see so thank you 🙌🏼 also thank you to everyone who came to our shows on this tour. It’s been such a blessing to be able to share this experience with you all ❤️ you guys always give me so many reasons to be grateful especially when I really need it 💜💜💜

Question: What happened with management and venue workers. What did they do bad?
Answer: Basically they knew we were coming because they're the ones who sold and provided the tickets and even had the poster of the show up. Our name was even written on the theater light thing etc. They knew we had a show that day as well. A mutal friend who works with my sisters boyfriend chad gilbert who is on new found glory (He was on tour as well but had to fly home due to a family emergency so please keep in your prayers and thoughts). Booked the show for us and we even had payed to use their venue.provided all the information they would need and so on. So we arrive to the venue, its freezing cold. We also had a street team that was given early access passes and special rewards for promoting us/ spreading word etc. We had to do soundcheck and make sure our equipment and everything was set up, lights worked, tech was all good. We all had to show IDs individually, like why? How do you not know who the band is and when theyre performing etc? Then they refused to let us inside the venue for like 15+ minutes left us standing there in the cold. When they finally let us in we got everything set up and sorted with the equipment and so on. Meet and greet came around and I believe the doors weren't open on time as well the security was being really rude to members of the fandom that were getting their turns to meet us and pictures etc. Telling fans to hurry up as they were handing out letters or whatever. So I was getting really ticked off and just wanted to call them out on it. I feel bad for how many of them were treated like that and its poor training on the theaters behalf.

Question: THIS WEEK/ MONTH WITH LAUREN
Answer:
This week with Lauren ✨
  
  lol again, this is more like the last ~ few weeks ~ with Lauren. Been such a crazy month !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Well really a crazy last 2 months. We have been working SO HARD trying to get this year all finished out for you guys. Planning our best videos, trying a lot of new things, finishing up our TOUR, coming out with our winter merch line, jewelry line, and BOOK Believe In You !!!! In the midst of all of thisss I’ve been trying to cultivate balance in my life 🕊 it’s been difficult for sure bc I have a tendency to be a bit of a workaholic 😅 I’m like oh yeah I can do everything ! I can stay up late ! I can wake up early ! I can ignore my friends ! And myself ! And literally everything else ! But .... that ain’t it. I reposted a quote on my story today that sums it up real well. It talks about doing your best and how you do your best when you take care of yourself. You do your best when you are healthy and happy. Doing your best is not running yourself into the ground til you can barely function. Trying to accept that. The biggest thing I’ve been trying to change is making the choice to do things for myself even if it means sacrificing something else. Like going to bed when I know I need more sleep, being 5 minutes late when I need to grab something I forgot instead of just going without it, canceling plans when I need a night to myself. Bc when life gets so busy, you’re going to have to sacrifice something and I am NOT sacrificing myself. Neither should you. The world will keep turning and you will be fine if you don’t do every last thing people expect of you and you take the time you need to take care of yourself instead. 💜
